\paragraph{Key Insight}
The TRTS results demonstrate that a classifier trained solely on synthetic data can generalise effectively to real-world samples, achieving strong performance across all attack types. In particular, it enables reliable identification of \textit{AP\_no} and \textit{AE\_no}, which were not detectable using residual-based methods.

These findings suggest that the generated data captures key structural properties of system behaviour relevant for classification, although subtle attacks such as \textit{AE\_no} remain more challenging.

Overall, the classification stage complements the residual-based detector: the detector captures strong deviations, while the classifier provides finer-grained identification, including for attacks that do not produce large observable residuals.
